      {
        "content": "Education and books are fundamental in acquiring knowledge as they amass centuries of collective human understanding. Through learning from others, we access diverse perspectives, theories, and facts that have been rigorously tested and validated. This external wisdom serves as a foundation upon which individuals can build further insights. While self-examination is valuable, it is the structured accumulation of knowledge from educators and scholars that equips one with the critical tools needed for deeper inquiry and understanding. Without education, the scope of our knowledge would be limited to personal experience and introspection alone.",
