      {
        "content": "Education encourages critical thinking and questioning. It is not merely the passive acceptance of information, but an active engagement with ideas. Good educators and well-written books teach us not only facts but also how to critically analyze them. Through this process, learners develop the ability to question, challenge, and refine their understanding. Furthermore, education exposes us to various viewpoints, prompting us to consider alternatives and deepen our self-examination. Thus, learning from others becomes a dynamic process that fosters inquiry and enriches personal understanding, rather than stifling it.",
